Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.17,0:00:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,CESKE ORPHANAGE
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.42,0:00:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough of you, young man!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.67,0:00:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When will you stop running away from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.34,0:00:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it again and you'll get no dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.55,0:00:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand, Milosz?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.05,0:00:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.01,0:00:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Get your hands out of your pockets\Nwhen you speak!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.23,0:00:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.52,0:00:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.77,0:00:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I do. It was that blonde woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.06,0:00:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And you saw her on Dominican Street?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.11,0:00:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She must live near there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.94,0:00:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How come you didn't follow her home?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.91,0:00:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't help it. I was starving.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.78,0:00:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll just have to find her ourselves\Nand turn her in to the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.50,0:00:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way Mr. Grimmer killed Gramps!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.04,0:00:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll prove he's innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.42,0:00:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Prove he's innocent?\NWill that help Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.38,0:00:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! We'll plan it right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.55,0:00:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosz, hurry up and finish your dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.78,0:02:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's where the unlicensed orphanage was,\Nwhere the first murder happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.66,0:02:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The former director\Nof Kinderheim 511 was killed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.71,0:02:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids say a blonde woman left\Nthe building just after the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.09,0:02:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The former director conducted\Nexperiments here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.51,0:02:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was the opposite\Nof what he did at Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.68,0:02:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to see what would happen\Nwhen he gave the children love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.56,0:03:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want to do?\NDo you want to go inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.52,0:03:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure the police have\Ntaken away all the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.69,0:03:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,-Mr. Grimmer, what are those?\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.15,0:03:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"To the police. Mr. Grimmer is innocent."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.19,0:03:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,"To the detectives.\NThe murderer is a blonde woman."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.78,0:03:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They're from those kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.66,0:03:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids who were at this orphanage\Ncame and posted these here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.33,0:03:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.92,0:03:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"To Mr. Grimmer."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.09,0:03:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan Bouček. That's a famous\Nsoccer player's trading card.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.34,0:03:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To those kids, it's very precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.06,0:03:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I react?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.43,0:03:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In these kinds of situations,\Nwhat expression should I make?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.32,0:03:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,At Kinderheim 511,\Nall emotions were removed from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.57,0:04:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, I was taught how to express\Nvarious emotions at that weird school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.78,0:04:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But these kinds of situations are\Nthe most difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.46,0:04:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the proper way to react?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.25,0:04:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you go and see those kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.01,0:04:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,SAINT BARDEJOV ORPHANAGE
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.22,0:04:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.26,0:04:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The children are always talking about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.02,0:04:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They're still out playing\Nand haven't come back yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.40,0:04:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope they return soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.44,0:04:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, have a look at their diaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.03,0:04:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They're full\Nof what are more like letters to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.78,0:04:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mr. Grimmer, let's play soccer again."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.99,0:04:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mr. Grimmer, you're bad at soccer,\Nso I'll teach you how to play."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.50,0:04:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mr. Grimmer,\Ncome play with all of us again."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.29,0:04:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, I'm smiling, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.71,0:04:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I had to learn to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.26,0:05:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned how to make this smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.06,0:05:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I find it hard to believe\Nthey remember me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.69,0:05:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why they think about me so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.32,0:05:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because they like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.61,0:05:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.28,0:05:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Long ago, when my child died,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.58,0:05:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to think about how to react.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.87,0:05:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.54,0:05:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How much should I cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.21,0:05:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I wail and scream?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.88,0:05:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I gnash my teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.22,0:05:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, I don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.68,0:05:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.56,0:05:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.36,0:05:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Antonin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.90,0:06:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer, there's big trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.99,0:06:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Antonin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.36,0:06:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids at Ceske Orphanage contacted us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.37,0:06:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There's been trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.37,0:06:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down, Antonin.\NTell me calmly what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.08,0:06:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They found that blonde woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.42,0:06:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, they watched for her\Nto find out where she lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.30,0:06:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But then Milosz…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.55,0:06:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosz disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.26,0:06:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,KRUMLOV NATIONAL HOSPITAL
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.18,0:06:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.89,0:06:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So the people\Nwho have come to visit you recently
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.27,0:06:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,are a middle-aged gentleman,\Na tall German,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.23,0:06:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and a long-haired Japanese man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.57,0:06:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.40,0:06:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Incidentally,\Nyou're forgetting one other visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.78,0:06:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The nurse told me that\Na long-haired blonde woman visited you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.66,0:06:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman? No. No woman visited me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.92,0:07:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the nurse remembers very clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.51,0:07:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She was very beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.47,0:07:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she was very pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.09,0:07:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.52,0:07:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.35,0:07:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.10,0:07:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosz.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.40,0:07:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I met you before?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.40,0:07:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.49,0:07:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you doing on the street?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.78,0:07:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.08,0:07:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You often walk around here, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.33,0:07:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.67,0:07:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.04,0:07:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.67,0:07:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to stand.\NHave a seat and drink some juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.56,0:07:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you moving out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.93,0:07:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.23,0:08:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got that big bag\Nand there's nothing in this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.15,0:08:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is your mom around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.66,0:08:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.74,0:08:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you're looking for your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.75,0:08:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBut I don't know if she's around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.29,0:08:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how will you find her?\NDo you have a photo of her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.30,0:08:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.17,0:08:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you don't know what she looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.68,0:08:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.14,0:08:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If I see her face, I'll know!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.22,0:08:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody at the orphanage believes me.\NThey say there's no way I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.18,0:08:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'll know my mom when I see her!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.10,0:08:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.60,0:08:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.19,0:08:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom will know me when she sees me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.87,0:08:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What if she acts like she doesn't know you\Neven when she finds you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.66,0:08:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.54,0:09:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure she wanted you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.29,0:09:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did she abandon you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.67,0:09:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't she abandon you\Nbecause she hates you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.97,0:09:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.18,0:09:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Being born really is quite special,\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.31,0:09:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.81,0:09:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, nearly everything\Nin this universe is death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.15,0:09:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to this universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.98,0:09:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a life born here in some corner of Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.32,0:09:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is just a moment's flash.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.12,0:09:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Death is what's normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.70,0:09:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we live?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.04,0:09:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because someone wanted us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.25,0:09:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wanted you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.51,0:09:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the reason for you to even live?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.39,0:09:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A long-haired blonde woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.85,0:10:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that must be Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.77,0:10:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this Anna woman live nearby?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.86,0:10:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think she lives in an apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.32,0:10:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in the dead-end alley\Naround the second corner down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.78,0:10:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a nice girl.\NShe's always so sweet and says hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.54,0:10:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna? I know her. She's a nice girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.96,0:10:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,She always smiles and says hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.46,0:10:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what floor and room she's in?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.09,0:10:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. That's it up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.63,0:10:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's her window on the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.56,0:10:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If what the kids said is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.18,0:10:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and if the boy\NMilosz has been kidnapped by her,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.10,0:10:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and if this Anna woman living here is\Nthat woman…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.78,0:10:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And if this woman is the person\Nthat I think they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.03,0:10:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,then I can put an end to all this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.63,0:11:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,She's gotten away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.64,0:11:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Where has Milosz gone off to?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.19,0:11:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Where was he taken?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.44,0:11:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He went after this blonde woman\Nto prove my innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.82,0:11:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.49,0:11:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I react\Nin this kind of situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.79,0:11:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Those kids have been put in danger\Nbecause they tried to prove my innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.09,0:11:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember what those kids said?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.46,0:11:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They said Milosz always\Nwalks the streets of Prague,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.22,0:11:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,searching for his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.47,0:12:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to find his mother, does he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.47,0:12:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When my own child died,\NI didn't feel a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.77,0:12:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,One day when I was working at a newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.65,0:12:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a female co-worker started talking to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.86,0:12:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,She said she loved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.32,0:12:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I married her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.41,0:12:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd been taught that getting married\Nmade me less suspicious
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.45,0:12:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,when doing spy work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.92,0:12:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She became pregnant and we had a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.96,0:12:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one day,\Nmy wife was out shopping nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.13,0:12:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When I entered my child's room,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.80,0:12:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he was lying face down\Nand wasn't breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.10,0:12:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave him CPR and called the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.06,0:12:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I did everything I should do…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.98,0:12:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,without hesitating.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.52,0:12:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But my child died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.07,0:12:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,At the funeral, my wife got angry with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.99,0:13:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,"How can you be so calm?\NHow come you're not crying?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.37,0:13:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"You've always been that way!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.96,0:13:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"You were that way with me too!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.08,0:13:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"You can't love anyone!\NYour heart is an empty hole!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.92,0:13:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And then… my wife left me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.09,0:13:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to find Milosz.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.81,0:13:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You said that Milosz\Nwas the child of a prostitute
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.77,0:13:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,who works in the red light district\Nat the Czech border.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.35,0:13:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.56,0:13:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If the person who was here is\Nthe person that I think they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.28,0:13:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think they'll let the boy live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.45,0:13:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But they won't simply kill the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.12,0:13:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is who I think it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.91,0:13:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll have the boy undergo the cruelest\Nthing possible before killing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.92,0:14:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go down this road,\Nyou'll be in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.30,0:14:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And my mom's down this road?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.51,0:14:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a bustling town just up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.85,0:14:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where I can find her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.06,0:14:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.48,0:14:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Go by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.06,0:14:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll know your mother when you see her,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.69,0:14:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and she'll know you when she sees you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.32,0:14:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But if nobody wants to talk to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.36,0:14:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,then that means nobody wanted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.08,0:14:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.91,0:14:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.50,0:14:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.64,0:14:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.96,0:15:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The cruelest thing, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.23,0:15:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.82,0:15:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.15,0:15:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.11,0:15:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.99,0:15:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You are? For who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.91,0:15:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.95,0:15:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.91,0:15:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.79,0:16:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.79,0:16:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I know your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.47,0:16:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is she? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.18,0:16:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.97,0:16:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that around here there are about\N50 women who could be her!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.02,0:16:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did she abandon you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.36,0:16:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! My boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.61,0:16:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My boy! My boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.65,0:16:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you, lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.24,0:16:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now. It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.82,0:16:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.12,0:16:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,-Just let me hold you.\N-Who the heck is that kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.29,0:16:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not really your kid, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.80,0:16:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.26,0:16:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd never do something as dumb as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.47,0:16:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you got the clap on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.31,0:16:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Screw you! You got a problem? Come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.85,0:16:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, cut that out! Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.69,0:17:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! Not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.56,0:17:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I paid my money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.94,0:17:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the customer,\Nso do as the customer says.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.07,0:17:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.24,0:17:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And a kid's watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.16,0:17:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.83,0:17:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch this. Don't run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.58,0:17:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a teacher in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.54,0:17:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm liked by the kids\Nand by their parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.80,0:17:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a wonderful and gentlemanly teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.80,0:17:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a wonderful teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.40,0:17:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.11,0:17:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wanted you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.74,0:17:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey boy, give me money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.53,0:17:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sick, lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.49,0:17:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm about to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.08,0:17:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.62,0:18:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you listening?\NBecause I'm about to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.96,0:18:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Money… Give me money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.25,0:18:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all I've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.43,0:18:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly everything\Nin this universe is death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.77,0:18:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wanted you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.90,0:18:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the reason for you to even live?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.29,0:18:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.09,0:18:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.81,0:19:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the end of the red light district.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.23,0:19:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Several people in the town\Nsaid they saw Milosz.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.07,0:19:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.74,0:19:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He could still be in the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.58,0:19:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosz!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.55,0:19:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosz.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.60,0:19:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.68,0:19:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.56,0:19:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.57,0:19:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You worked so very hard for my sake
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.82,0:19:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to prove that I'm innocent, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.45,0:20:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right now. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.51,0:20:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.39,0:20:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I doing this right, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.90,0:20:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe I should cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.49,0:20:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I never learned how to deal\Nwith this complex kind of feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.46,0:20:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you do that, Milosz?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.72,0:21:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.43,0:21:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What have you seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.35,0:21:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you told?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.07,0:21:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosz, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.32,0:21:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.70,0:21:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But… even so…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.62,0:21:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a reason that you were born!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.04,0:21:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You were born because somebody wanted you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.67,0:21:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it. I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.76,0:21:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody wanted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.80,0:21:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.69,0:22:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Dr. Tenma,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.99,0:22:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm saying is right, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.33,0:22:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.25,0:22:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the expression…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.58,0:22:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,on my face now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.42,0:22:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're crying.
